1.text: Yawn or chew gum to open your eustachian tubes.

2.text: Try the Toynbee maneuver to unclog your ears.

3.text: Do the valsalva maneuver to relieve pressure.

4.text: Use steam to thin your earwax.

5.text: Apply a warm compress to drain the fluid in your ear.

6.text: Dry the fluid in your ear with a mixture of a vinegar and water.

7.text: Soften your earwax with a few drops of oil.

8.text: Take a decongestant if manual methods don’t work.

9.text: Use a nasal spray with antihistamine if you have allergies.

10.text: See a healthcare provider if the issue persists.
